23/02/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- Kosovo's interim government endorsed a plan Tuesday (22 February) for local government reform.
The concept, prepared by the working group for decentralisation, provides for the administrative division of Kosovo into five new municipalities -- Gracanica, Hani i Elezit (Djeneral Jankovic), Junik, Mamusa and Partes.
Prime Minister Ramush Haradinaj also confirmed Tuesday that talks between Belgrade and Pristina on the issue of missing persons would begin on 10 March in Belgrade.
(KosovaLive, Tanjug, B92 - 22/02/05)
